===Etymology 2===
Middle English ''[[gomme]]'', from Old French ''[[gome]]'', from Late Latin ''[[gumma]]'', from {{L.}}Latin ''[[gummi]]'', from Greek ''[[κόμμι]]'', of Egyptian origin

====Noun====
{{en-noun-reg-both|gum}}

#{{uncountable}} any of various [[viscous]] or [[sticky]] [[substance]]s that are [[exude]]d by certain [[plant]]s
#{{uncountable}} any [[viscous]] or [[sticky]] [[substance]] resembling those that are [[exude]]d by certain [[plant]]s
#{{uncountable}} [[chewing gum]]
#{{countable}} a single piece of [[chewing gum]]
#:''Do you have a gum I could have?''

